<h2><a name="config">XML System Configuration file</h2>
<hr>
<p>The XML System Configuration file allows defining the value of the platform configuration paramenters. Number of processors in a SMP system, size of caches, bandwidth of a bus or memory delay are possible configuration parameters.</p>

<p>File structure:</p>

<pre>
&lt; simulator_input_interface &gt;	
	&lt; parameter name="mem_size" value="256" /&gt;
	&lt; parameter name="num_proc" value="3"   /&gt;
	...
&lt; /simulator_input_interface &gt;
</pre>

<hr>
<h2>Parameter use:</h2>
Paarameter defined values are used to replace the parameter names in the XML System Description file. The parameter to be replaced is named with the same name starting with "__".

<p>Example:</p>
<pre>
XML System Configuration file:
	
	...
	&lt; parameter name="msize" value="256" /&gt;
	...

XML System Description file:

	...
	&lt; HW_Component name="memory" mem_size="__msize" /&gt;
	...
</pre>


